config.text:
Welcome to the RIVaL Data Collection Hub!

Check out the content and links below for a detailed explanation of this project, the current status and more information about how you can access the data and imagery.

config.placeholder: Double click to edit text
config.text: Our Collection Status Dashboard provides a dynamic view of your state's imagery and LiDAR collection﻿.

config.placeholder: Double click to edit text
config.text: We want to ensure that we are providing your state with the highest quality extraction possible. DOT staff are encouraged to review and provide feedback on these extracted assets using our Data Review App.

config.placeholder: Double click to edit text
config.text: The Data Dictionary provides a complete breakdown of the schema for our extracted assets. Both attributes and their corresponding values are defined for every extracted dataset.

config.placeholder: Double click to edit text
config.text: When extracting assets along your state's roadways, we do our utmost to adhere to the agreed upon data dictionary. However, there are always unexpected circumstances along the way which may fall outside of the norm. The Extraction Details log documents as many scenarios as we could find and provides our reasoning.

config.placeholder: Double click to edit text

config.text: ﻿The Data Dictionary contains a detailed listing of attributes and other characteristics for every extracted data asset.

﻿Step 1: Choose your Data
Step 3: Select and Check Data

﻿Welcome to your data review portal. The purpose of this page is to provide an opportunity for you to review your "Phase 0" dataset from Cyclomedia.


Click the right arrow below to learn about each step of the review process.

1. Select a feature on the map

If you notice an issue, click and select that feature on the map.


2. Fill out the Feedback Form

Using the "Asset Feedback" panel to the left, fill out the form and describe what you've found.


3. Submit the Form

Once all required fields are complete, press "Submit" at the bottom.
